flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|narrowing_1|1|Keeping the work private too long|You may continue refining the work alone after it has reached the point where another person could help sharpen it.|social_exchange|active|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::narrowing_1
flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|narrowing_2|2|Thinking harder when a reset would help|When attention gets stuck, you may try to solve it with more focus. A change of pace or movement may be more useful.|physical_rhythm|active|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::narrowing_2
flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|narrowing_3|3|Opening ideas without choosing the next step|Creative Movement can refresh the work, but it can also add more options when the useful move is to decide what to finish.|creative_movement|active|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::narrowing_3
13_Application
domain_key|pattern_key|application_area|guidance_type|priority|guidance_text|linked_signal_key|status|lookup_key
flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|use_this_when|guidance|1|Use this pattern when the work needs careful judgement, original thinking, or a first version that cannot be rushed. Give yourself a focused block before meetings, feedback, or group input.|deep_focus|active|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::use_this_when
flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|watch_for|guidance|2|Watch for the moment when you are polishing privately instead of learning anything new. That is often the point to move, pause, or ask one useful person what is clear and what is not.|social_exchange|active|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::watch_for
flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|develop_by|guidance|3|Develop by sharing a rough version earlier than you normally would. Choose someone who can test clarity without taking over the direction of the work.|social_exchange|active|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::develop_by
14_Closing_Integration
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|closing_summary|core_gift|core_trap|development_edge|memorable_line|status|lookup_key
flow_state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|concentrated|This result points to a flow style built around depth, then range. You are likely to do your best work when you first have space to understand the problem, then use ideas, movement, and one well-timed conversation to make the work clearer.|Your gift is the ability to turn sustained attention into thoughtful, original work.|The trap is staying inside your own process after the work would benefit from response.|The useful edge is to share the work while it is still flexible, not only when it feels complete.|Focus gives the work depth. A timely conversation helps it land.|active|flow_state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::concentrated
